pr_body: This needs a custom linker before it is ready.
pr_review_comments:
[{'comment_id': 706953748, 'comment_body': "`gfortran` -> `GnuFortranCompiler`
`lfortran` -> `LFortranFortranCompiler` ?

I believe a better class name for this (so that people don't wonder what a FortranFortran compiler is) would be `LLVMFortranCompiler`", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 9, 13, 1, 46, 40, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'eli-schwartz', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 707277194, 'comment_body': "I'd like that but it isn't unambiguous. Flang is also an LLVM compiler (and part of LLVM core nowadays)", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 9, 13, 12, 16, 22, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'HaoZeke', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 708769067, 'comment_body': "Which we already support, and I'm pretty sure it's called either FlangFortran or ClangFortran", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 9, 15, 1, 28, 6, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'dcbaker', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 708793809, 'comment_body': 'Well, that seems annoying. :/ Dunno what to suggest for a better name.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 9, 15, 2, 42, 50, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'eli-schwartz', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 708803072, 'comment_body': 'How about just `LFortranCompiler` or `LFFortranCompiler`?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 9, 15, 3, 10, 23, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'dcbaker', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 710193759, 'comment_body': 'I think `LFortranCompiler` sounds good; thanks ^_^', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 9, 16, 14, 48, 52, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'HaoZeke', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 710695861, 'comment_body': "I know nothing about fortran. What's the meaning of this change?", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 9, 17, 3, 8, 42, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'eli-schwartz', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 710960042, 'comment_body': "Ah, sorry; actually this one is an incomplete fix for fortran compilers which was more fully fleshed out in #9248; I shouldn't have put this here. ", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 9, 17, 11, 0, 52, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'HaoZeke', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 710961233, 'comment_body': 'Essentially a complete fortran (90) program to test with is:

```fortran
program main
print *, "Hello"
end program
```

Which can be written as `program main; print*, "Fortran compilation is working."; end program`

Depending on the standards; some compilers accept not having `program` in the beginning (`F77`); and others accept not explicitly requiring `end program`.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 9, 17, 11, 3, 3, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'HaoZeke', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 714502720, 'comment_body': 'The other PR is merged now, so you can "put this here" by rebasing. :D', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 9, 23, 6, 28, 30, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'eli-schwartz', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 716058836, 'comment_body': "I just got code merged that also add the default search path here, which is necessary when combining different compiler family's (GCC and lfortran,  for example).", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 9, 25, 15, 59, 8, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'dcbaker', 'type': 'User'}]
